			<description><![CDATA[<p>
The Public Relations and Marketing Communications Manager will execute PR and marketing programs that build brand reputation, drive increased visibility for Acumatica as a leader in developing cloud-based ERP applications for small and mid-sized businesses internationally, and drive developer interest in joining the company in Russia.&nbsp; The position will be primarily focused on Russia and other international markets outside of the Americas.&nbsp; The position will be based in our offices in Moscow, or our Headquarters in the US (based on willingness of the candidate to travel).</p>
<p>
<strong>Summary of Key Responsibilities:</strong><br />
&bull; Reporting to the Director of Communications, will help develop and grow the visibility for our brand.<br />
&bull; Execute PR and marketing programs that increase awareness and coverage of the Acumatica Brand.<br />
&bull; Build &amp; promote Acumatica Employer brand through Russian language company website, industry events &amp; PR<br />
&bull; Manage Press, Analyst and other influencer relationships in Russia and other International markets in Europe, Asia and Africa.<br />
&bull; Manage and create Russian and English content, including blogs, newsletters, press releases and marketing materials for a variety of internal and external outlets<br />
&bull; Drive Russian social media activities to enhance brand profile as best-in-class employer for engineers. Engage and enable our Russian R&amp;D team to support our social media efforts.<br />
&bull; Manage Russian-language company website<br />
&bull; Drive press coverage of company in Russian media, including placing executives at high-profile industry events<br />
&bull; Field media inquiries and represent company at industry events to build presence<br />
&bull; Manage and maintain all-up editorial and events calendar<br />
&bull; Outreach, briefings, and relationship building with international press and analysts (excluding Americas &ndash; US, Canada and Latin America)<br />
&bull; Work closely with engineering team in Moscow to elevate profile of Acumatica in developer community</p>
<p>
<strong>Desired Skills and Experience</strong><br />
&bull; Bachelor&#39;s degree in communications, public relations, journalism or related fields<br />
&bull; Minimum of 5 years&#39; relevant work experience (ideally in the ICT industry)<br />
&bull; Experience in marketing communications in both Russian and English language<br />
&bull; Deep working knowledge of social media and successful track record executing and delivering programs<br />
&bull; Proficiency working with Microsoft Office (Google Analytics a plus)<br />
&bull; Exceptional written and verbal communication skills in Russian and English<br />
&bull; Ability to work in fast-paced environment while balancing multiple priorities<br />
&bull; Familiarity and confidence working in all media<br />
&bull; Ability to coordinate multiple and diverse projects simultaneously and under deadline<br />
&bull; Superb collaboration and interpersonal skills<br />
&bull; International PR experience in Europe or Asia (in addition to Russia) is a big plus.<br />
<strong>Company Description</strong><br />
Acumatica, the fastest-growing provider of cloud-based ERP applications for small and mid-sized businesses, is looking for a PR and Marketing Communications Manager for its Moscow office. The company, based in Kirkland, WA, with offices worldwide, sells financial management, distribution, CRM, and project accounting software through a global partner channel.&nbsp;</p>
